
1. npm init
2. npm i nodemon
3. npm run server




4. npm i (before file)
4 ============================
1. install babel packages

cmd: npm i @babel/node @babel/core @babel/cli @babel/preset-env
2. create .babelrc file in root
.babelrc =>

{
    "presets": ["@babel/preset-env"]

}

3. create script for babel with nodemon in package.json



4.. install mongoose
cmd:> npm i mongoose

5.install express
cmd:> npm i express


6.install body-perser
cmd:> npm i body-parser


====================
user - Name , Email, (optional - Password, Contact)
category - Name , Alias
Product - Name, Category, Price, Quantity, Description, Image


remove file from drive in backend use fs.unlink